  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Missiles<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Research Preference: Energy<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Paratis</span> are a human-=
sized
  insectoid aquatic species.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Paratis</span> are very pas=
sive in
  nature. Even amongst themselves, they live mostly in isolation, coming
  together begrudgingly to cooperate to achieve similar goals.<o:p></o:p></=
p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Still, <span class=3DSpellE>Paratis</span> are not
  trustworthy despite their seemingly placid nature, they spend large amoun=
ts
  of time plotting their own advancement at the expense of others.<o:p></o:=
p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Paratis</span> deep knowled=
ge of
  missile weaponry has culminated in the development of the <span class=3DS=
pellE>Paratis</span>
  Hammerhead, a missile system that is remarkably quick yet yields a
  surprisingly large payload.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span=
>Range
  of this weapon system is limited, however, but the raw firepower makes up=
 for
  this.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Unique to the <span class=3DSpellE>Paratis</span> is=
 The
  Game, an elaborate sport that acts out wars in elaborate social displays =
of
  debate, intrigue and political maneuvering. This game is a combination of
  competitive, social and training that draw <span class=3DSpellE>Paratis</=
span>
  together more than any other possible reason for interaction. This game c=
an
  vary in level of brutality depending on the stakes but is also a form of
  entertainment transmitted for leisure. Their greatest heroes are often the
  best at the sport.</p>
